WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:00.710 --> 00:00:03.370
Get moving right now, get moving right now

3
00:00:03.590 --> 00:00:06.460
Hoisting our flag high, we'll make it somehow

4
00:00:12.770 --> 00:00:15.500
Setting out all on our own to cross the endless sea,

5
00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:18.060
you know what we're searching for

6
00:00:18.860 --> 00:00:21.810
The worldwide enigma, treasures undiscovered

7
00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:23.940
Picking's ripe, so let's go explore

8
00:00:24.820 --> 00:00:27.960
We're all so excited, our hearts can't keep quiet

9
00:00:27.960 --> 00:00:29.710
Nothing left to do but press on

10
00:00:29.710 --> 00:00:35.590
Trailing after footprints left by the dreamers before us

11
00:00:36.420 --> 00:00:39.390
Stormy nights can try their best to sink us

12
00:00:39.390 --> 00:00:42.390
We'll sail on, if we just stick together

13
00:00:42.390 --> 00:00:46.540
Try and stop us if you can

14
00:00:46.680 --> 00:00:47.860
We always pull through

15
00:00:48.760 --> 00:00:51.590
Get moving right now, get moving right now

16
00:00:51.720 --> 00:00:54.550
Hoisting our flag high, we'll make it somehow

17
00:00:54.600 --> 00:00:57.140
Even if we sometimes shed tears,

18
00:00:57.230 --> 00:01:00.580
and want to hide them from prying eyes

19
00:01:00.770 --> 00:01:03.520
But go and chase it, yeah, go and chase it

20
00:01:03.690 --> 00:01:06.520
Run the direction the compass points in

21
00:01:06.610 --> 00:01:09.230
All our dreams are straight ahead it says

22
00:01:09.230 --> 00:01:11.400
So don't sit back, let's chase it

23
00:01:18.830 --> 00:01:21.490
Get moving right now, get moving right now

24
00:01:21.800 --> 00:01:24.540
We have to pull through ahead of them all

25
00:01:24.630 --> 00:01:27.120
If we hold firm and stand our ground,

26
00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:30.540
I know the future's within our grasp

27
00:01:30.600 --> 00:01:33.630
So go and chase it, yeah, go and chase it

28
00:01:33.680 --> 00:01:36.510
The world's our oyster, it's waiting for us

29
00:01:36.560 --> 00:01:38.930
All the sadness and the joy we see,

30
00:01:39.150 --> 00:01:41.430
let's etch it in our hearts

31
00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:54.300
<b>Unprecedented</b>

32
00:02:00.600 --> 00:02:01.930
Hey, Gomorrah!

33
00:02:01.930 --> 00:02:04.650
Why are you slamming into the walls?!

34
00:02:04.650 --> 00:02:06.980
What's wrong? Did you
finally reach your limit?

35
00:02:12.150 --> 00:02:14.700
Th-That's not it! He can't see!

36
00:02:14.700 --> 00:02:17.410
With his retinas damaged,
his eyesight is weakening!

37
00:02:20.830 --> 00:02:23.710
What?! You can't see?!

38
00:02:27.750 --> 00:02:29.670
It set off in a crazy dash!

39
00:02:29.670 --> 00:02:31.420
Keep them encircled!

40
00:02:31.420 --> 00:02:32.840
Stop the monster!

41
00:02:32.840 --> 00:02:35.640
What're you doing?!
Fire the trench mortars already!

42
00:02:38.100 --> 00:02:40.350
Stop, Gomorrah!

43
00:02:40.350 --> 00:02:42.850
You're in no shape to keep going!

44
00:02:46.060 --> 00:02:48.860
He says that he promised Sodom!

45
00:02:51.150 --> 00:02:54.200
He told Sodom, "Leave the rest to me!

46
00:02:54.200 --> 00:02:59.530
I'll carry everyone for the both of us!"

47
00:03:00.010 --> 00:03:01.620
G-Gomorrah...

48
00:03:05.920 --> 00:03:08.040
They were inside its stomach?

49
00:03:08.040 --> 00:03:11.840
I can't eat anymore. I'm full.

50
00:03:11.840 --> 00:03:13.880
Take 'em back home as emergency food.

51
00:03:16.630 --> 00:03:18.430
Bro! There's trouble!

52
00:03:18.430 --> 00:03:21.100
Some pirates beat up Sodom and Gomorrah!

53
00:03:22.060 --> 00:03:25.560
You've got some nerve
messing with my underlings!

54
00:03:31.320 --> 00:03:36.570
Hey, you're injured!
Don't dance, Sodom and Gomorrah!

55
00:03:43.160 --> 00:03:46.580
There's a dead end ahead!
He'll die if he crashes into it!

56
00:03:46.580 --> 00:03:49.130
Gomorroah! Stop! Don't rush around blindly!

57
00:03:49.630 --> 00:03:50.920
Stop!

58
00:03:52.420 --> 00:03:53.920
A dead end?

59
00:03:53.920 --> 00:03:55.300
Do you see one?

60
00:03:55.300 --> 00:03:56.880
Nope...

61
00:03:56.880 --> 00:03:58.890
I don't see anything like that.

62
00:04:35.710 --> 00:04:38.300
It's the courthouse, Gomorrah!

63
00:04:43.140 --> 00:04:46.100
W-We made it! Gomorrah!

64
00:04:48.270 --> 00:04:49.560
Reporting to all units!

65
00:04:49.560 --> 00:04:53.560
<b>Courthouse</b>

66
00:04:49.560 --> 00:04:53.020
The pirates' king bull broke through
the encirclement in Block D!

67
00:04:49.680 --> 00:04:53.560
<b>Tower of Justice</b>

68
00:04:53.020 --> 00:04:55.940
They've reached the courthouse plaza!

69
00:04:55.940 --> 00:04:58.110
I repeat! The pirates...!

70
00:05:01.280 --> 00:05:04.080
Look at this, Funkfreed.

71
00:05:06.330 --> 00:05:08.750
It's a golden transponder snail.

72
00:05:09.210 --> 00:05:14.460
As it gives you the authority
to exercise a buster call,

73
00:05:14.460 --> 00:05:20.420
you can't carry this glittering transponder snail
without authority from at least a Marine admiral.

74
00:05:20.930 --> 00:05:26.510
In order for me to exercise a buster call,
Aokiji temporarily entrusted it to me.

75
00:05:28.140 --> 00:05:29.520
Just wait and see!

76
00:05:29.520 --> 00:05:34.480
Once the revival of the weapon becomes reality,
I'll hold this power at all times,

77
00:05:34.480 --> 00:05:40.030
and I'll no longer have to obtain an admiral's
special permission just to control troops.

78
00:05:45.490 --> 00:05:49.000
With the push of this one button,
an entire island will be wiped out.

79
00:05:50.830 --> 00:05:54.500
Authority is like a weapon too, huh?

80
00:05:54.500 --> 00:05:56.290
Chief Spandam!

81
00:05:57.880 --> 00:05:59.760
That scared me!

82
00:05:59.760 --> 00:06:01.010
What's your problem?!

83
00:06:01.010 --> 00:06:02.760
Knock first!

84
00:06:02.760 --> 00:06:04.720
I almost pressed the button!

85
00:06:05.090 --> 00:06:09.890
I-I'm sorry, but I was told
that this is an emergency.

86
00:06:09.890 --> 00:06:12.560
There's a call from Enies Lobby's main island.

87
00:06:12.890 --> 00:06:14.020
What?!

88
00:06:14.020 --> 00:06:17.570
A call?! They should've
called this room directly!

89
00:06:17.570 --> 00:06:20.860
Th– Hey! The receiver is off the hook!

90
00:06:20.860 --> 00:06:23.320
Who keeps doing that?!

91
00:06:24.320 --> 00:06:27.530
You just said that there's
an emergency or something, right?

92
00:06:27.530 --> 00:06:28.410
Yes, sir.

93
00:06:37.170 --> 00:06:38.170
Spanda!

94
00:06:46.010 --> 00:06:47.970
Hey, Nico Robin!

95
00:06:47.970 --> 00:06:52.600
Apparently there's an emergency report
from Enies Lobby's main island.

96
00:06:52.600 --> 00:06:57.100
It's probably not a real emergency,
but you can guess what it's about, right?

97
00:06:59.440 --> 00:07:03.650
After he fought so hard
to beat five of my guards,

98
00:07:03.650 --> 00:07:07.240
just picture poor little Straw Hat Luffy
being stomped into the ground

99
00:07:07.240 --> 00:07:13.500
by our strongest gatekeepers, Oimo and Kashi,
along with the rest of your friends.

100
00:07:16.250 --> 00:07:21.800
Let's listen together and hear what became of the idiots
who rebelled against the World Government!

101
00:07:21.800 --> 00:07:23.670
You're a real scumbag!

102
00:07:23.670 --> 00:07:25.220
Shut up, you punk!

103
00:07:29.260 --> 00:07:30.890
Hey, guard!

104
00:07:31.430 --> 00:07:33.520
Yeah, this is Spandam.

105
00:07:33.520 --> 00:07:35.980
Oh! Is that you, Chief?!

106
00:07:35.980 --> 00:07:38.480
Finally! I have a report you need to hear!

107
00:07:38.480 --> 00:07:40.310
Wh-Where do I start...?

108
00:07:41.940 --> 00:07:43.440
Calm down, you idiot!

109
00:07:43.440 --> 00:07:45.440
It's about the Straw Hats, isn't it?

110
00:07:45.440 --> 00:07:48.950
What happened since
the last report? Oh! Better yet...

111
00:07:49.320 --> 00:07:54.700
just summarize the key points
and make it loud and clear!

112
00:07:54.700 --> 00:07:55.790
Yes, sir! The invaders–

113
00:07:55.790 --> 00:07:57.920
You accidentally killed them?!

114
00:07:57.920 --> 00:08:00.210
Well, that's their own fault for being so weak–

115
00:08:00.210 --> 00:08:02.670
Approximately sixty pirate invaders...

116
00:08:03.380 --> 00:08:10.090
have breached the courthouse plaza,
the innermost point on the main island!

117
00:08:15.350 --> 00:08:17.810
Calling all units on Enies Lobby's main island!

118
00:08:17.810 --> 00:08:20.980
All soldiers! Head to
the courthouse plaza at once!

119
00:08:24.150 --> 00:08:26.360
You really pulled through, Gomorrah!

120
00:08:26.690 --> 00:08:30.240
I promise, you and your bro's
efforts won't go to waste!

121
00:08:32.580 --> 00:08:34.580
Let's give 'em hell, boys!

122
00:08:34.580 --> 00:08:37.120
We'll rescue Big Bro Franky!

123
00:08:37.120 --> 00:08:40.500
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

124
00:08:40.500 --> 00:08:44.630
The pirates have reached the courthouse plaza!

125
00:09:04.690 --> 00:09:06.190
Can you see Luffy?

126
00:09:06.190 --> 00:09:06.860
No.

127
00:09:12.660 --> 00:09:17.370
The rooftop's a little high for us
to scale the side of the building.

128
00:09:17.370 --> 00:09:20.210
Right. It's not like we're made of rubber.

129
00:09:21.040 --> 00:09:23.580
How many CP9 members did you see?

130
00:09:23.580 --> 00:09:26.840
We only saw the big horn guy.

131
00:09:28.010 --> 00:09:33.220
It's so surreal to think Robin and Franky
are up there with them in such a place.

132
00:09:34.350 --> 00:09:36.810
That aside, we have to hurry to Luffy!

133
00:09:36.810 --> 00:09:38.640
Robin is running out of time!

134
00:09:38.640 --> 00:09:40.810
Hurry to the courthouse plaza!

135
00:09:40.810 --> 00:09:43.150
The drawbridge isn't down yet! Corner them!

136
00:10:04.960 --> 00:10:07.040
Whoa! That frog's awesome!

137
00:10:07.040 --> 00:10:10.130
That's the flail that
knocked out Gomorrah! What a beast!

138
00:10:13.680 --> 00:10:16.220
Over there! They're running away!
I saw three of 'em!

139
00:10:17.350 --> 00:10:18.930
They're running now?

140
00:10:18.930 --> 00:10:20.350
But they attacked first!

141
00:10:20.350 --> 00:10:21.430
You idiot!

142
00:10:21.430 --> 00:10:25.270
It's a waste of time chasing after
each enemy who runs away!

143
00:10:41.830 --> 00:10:44.330
Shut up. I just went to check.

144
00:10:46.460 --> 00:10:50.170
It wouldn't hurt to know what kind of
enemies we're up against, would it?

145
00:10:50.170 --> 00:10:53.130
– Whoa! He brought him down!
– Whoa! He brought him down!

146
00:10:53.840 --> 00:10:55.550
What is this guy?!

147
00:10:55.550 --> 00:10:59.010
He's gotta be one helluva strong guy
to swing that thing around!

148
00:10:59.010 --> 00:11:02.100
Does he belong to a special
unit like the Watchdogs?

149
00:11:02.430 --> 00:11:05.310
There may be more hiding!

150
00:11:05.310 --> 00:11:06.350
Be careful.

151
00:11:09.230 --> 00:11:12.740
Let's scoot. The guards are closing in.

152
00:11:12.740 --> 00:11:14.240
Corner them!

153
00:11:14.240 --> 00:11:17.070
They'll never get those
heavy stone doors to budge!

154
00:11:17.070 --> 00:11:19.200
Finish them here in the plaza!

155
00:11:19.200 --> 00:11:22.660
Come to think of it, these doors are huge.

156
00:11:25.620 --> 00:11:27.040
How will we...

157
00:11:28.330 --> 00:11:30.040
get them open...?

158
00:11:32.550 --> 00:11:33.920
Get a move on!

159
00:11:33.920 --> 00:11:35.340
I'm going in!

160
00:11:35.340 --> 00:11:39.550
H-He cut through that thick stone!

161
00:11:39.550 --> 00:11:40.890
Zambai!

162
00:11:40.890 --> 00:11:46.690
We gotta split up and head to either side
to pull both of the drawbridge levers!

163
00:11:46.690 --> 00:11:49.020
O-Okay! You got this!

164
00:11:49.440 --> 00:11:52.270
Okay! This means we split into three teams!

165
00:11:53.150 --> 00:11:57.530
We're gonna clean up the courthouse,
so a few of you will come with me!

166
00:11:57.530 --> 00:11:59.990
Good luck to the rest of you! Now go!

167
00:12:07.580 --> 00:12:12.040
<b>Courthouse</b>
<b>Tower of Justice</b>

168
00:12:13.050 --> 00:12:13.920
Huh?

169
00:12:14.420 --> 00:12:19.390
Also, the giant gatekeepers, Oimo and Kashi,
went over to the pirates' side!

170
00:12:19.390 --> 00:12:22.640
They're speeding down the main road
toward the courthouse!

171
00:12:23.010 --> 00:12:25.220
Out of the way!

172
00:12:30.650 --> 00:12:33.650
Guard casualties have reached...

173
00:12:34.190 --> 00:12:36.030
over 2,000!

174
00:12:36.030 --> 00:12:38.280
N-Not five...?

175
00:12:38.280 --> 00:12:44.950
And the one who beat 1,000 all on his own,
Captain Straw Hat Luffy, suddenly disappeared...

176
00:12:44.950 --> 00:12:47.500
but we're searching for him as we speak!

177
00:12:48.790 --> 00:12:55.920
This has to be unprecedented—the worst
catastrophe in the history of Enies Lobby!

178
00:13:01.300 --> 00:13:02.930
Blueno...

179
00:13:02.930 --> 00:13:04.890
What's he doing over there?

180
00:13:08.310 --> 00:13:09.890
What's going on?

181
00:13:09.890 --> 00:13:16.610
What the hell is happening
on this island right now?!

182
00:13:17.320 --> 00:13:20.150
Baskerville! Chief Justice Baskerville!

183
00:13:20.150 --> 00:13:21.450
Come in! It's me!

184
00:13:21.910 --> 00:13:24.660
– Whoa! Chief Spandam!
– Whoa! Chief Spandam!

185
00:13:22.440 --> 00:13:24.660
<b>Courthouse</b>

186
00:13:24.660 --> 00:13:26.870
On the left: the Left Baskerville!

187
00:13:26.870 --> 00:13:28.950
On the right: the Right Baskerville!

188
00:13:29.460 --> 00:13:31.960
And in the center, I am...

189
00:13:31.960 --> 00:13:34.590
"Alone and Unafraid Along the Central Main Line"!

190
00:13:34.590 --> 00:13:35.460
– Just who is that?!
– Just who is that?!

191
00:13:35.460 --> 00:13:37.420
Give me a status report!

192
00:13:37.420 --> 00:13:41.430
I heard that the pirates have
already made it to the courthouse plaza!

193
00:13:41.430 --> 00:13:42.630
Status?

194
00:13:43.760 --> 00:13:45.300
Hm, status...

195
00:13:48.310 --> 00:13:49.770
As for the status...

196
00:13:50.730 --> 00:13:53.730
The plaza aside,
the inside of the courthouse...

197
00:13:54.360 --> 00:13:56.190
– ...is in a terribly horrible state!
– ...is in a terribly horrible state!

198
00:13:56.190 --> 00:13:57.730
What?!

199
00:14:04.070 --> 00:14:07.240
Ch-Chief Justice! I have a report!

200
00:14:07.240 --> 00:14:13.790
The pirates cut through the giant stone doors
and entered the courthouse!

201
00:14:13.790 --> 00:14:15.670
– I can see that already, you idiot!
– I can see that already, you idiot!

202
00:14:16.250 --> 00:14:18.750
I thought we'd see more enemies in here.

203
00:14:18.750 --> 00:14:22.130
Looks like the way is clear,
but what the heck is that?

204
00:14:24.930 --> 00:14:26.430
What?! His head...!

205
00:14:27.010 --> 00:14:29.350
It's like the story of the guard dog from hell!

206
00:14:29.350 --> 00:14:30.520
Berberus?!

207
00:14:30.520 --> 00:14:32.140
You mean Cerberus!

208
00:14:32.140 --> 00:14:34.270
Men! Order!

209
00:14:34.270 --> 00:14:37.020
This is a sacred chamber of law!

210
00:14:37.020 --> 00:14:42.110
We will now cast judgment
on your inevitable fate!

211
00:14:45.530 --> 00:14:46.910
All right, guys!

212
00:14:46.910 --> 00:14:49.280
Get to the rooftop to join up with Straw Hat!

213
00:14:49.660 --> 00:14:52.700
Yokozuna and the rest of us
will hold off enemies at the doors!

214
00:14:53.210 --> 00:14:57.210
We've got your back,
so just keep pushing forward!

215
00:14:57.210 --> 00:14:58.590
Got it.

216
00:14:58.590 --> 00:15:01.380
Hey, look at that.
The trial just started.

217
00:14:58.920 --> 00:15:01.380
Their crime is as follows!

218
00:15:01.380 --> 00:15:04.550
First, the act of stepping into Enies Lobby,

219
00:15:02.010 --> 00:15:04.720
Just ignore it! Which way do we go?!

220
00:15:04.550 --> 00:15:07.180
which belongs to the World Government, is...

221
00:15:04.720 --> 00:15:07.180
Straight ahead! There are stairs on both sides!

222
00:15:07.180 --> 00:15:08.720
Follow them to the top!

223
00:15:08.720 --> 00:15:09.850
All right!

224
00:15:10.470 --> 00:15:11.970
How rude!

225
00:15:11.970 --> 00:15:15.020
They ignored our sacred trial!

226
00:15:15.020 --> 00:15:17.980
Unforgivable! They dare
disrespect the Judicial Island?!

227
00:15:17.980 --> 00:15:19.360
Damn you! Die!

228
00:15:22.530 --> 00:15:25.700
Wh-What's going on? His swords
look like they're bending!

229
00:15:27.820 --> 00:15:30.330
Charming Demon Sleepless Night...

230
00:15:31.950 --> 00:15:33.370
Oni Giri!

231
00:15:41.040 --> 00:15:43.460
Is he the one who cut open the door?

232
00:15:47.300 --> 00:15:48.470
Okay, let's go.

233
00:15:48.470 --> 00:15:49.930
The path's wide open!

234
00:15:49.930 --> 00:15:50.680
Yep!

235
00:15:52.930 --> 00:15:56.890
How is a guy who's this
strong not the captain?

236
00:15:58.560 --> 00:16:02.400
Wait! Wait! Wait! Outta my way!
Reindeer! Swordsmoron!

237
00:16:03.150 --> 00:16:04.570
Bro with the suit...

238
00:16:04.570 --> 00:16:06.320
This is dangerous enemy territory!

239
00:16:06.320 --> 00:16:10.320
I'll clear the path so Nami can
move forward! Outta my way!

240
00:16:10.320 --> 00:16:11.030
Hey, watch it!

241
00:16:11.030 --> 00:16:13.540
What?! Why is he starting a fight?!

242
00:16:15.080 --> 00:16:16.750
You want a piece of me, bastard?!

243
00:16:17.160 --> 00:16:21.040
Shut up! You cretins are
not to get in Nami's way!

244
00:16:21.040 --> 00:16:23.630
Nami, this way! Follow only me!

245
00:16:24.170 --> 00:16:27.720
Hey, we came to rescue Robin, right?

246
00:16:29.470 --> 00:16:32.850
That's right, Robin is waiting
for me to rescue her!

247
00:16:32.850 --> 00:16:35.520
Could she be crying right now
out of loneliness?!

248
00:16:35.520 --> 00:16:37.020
Seriously...

249
00:16:39.390 --> 00:16:41.230
We look away for one second, and Zoro's...!

250
00:16:41.230 --> 00:16:42.560
What?!

251
00:16:42.560 --> 00:16:45.570
Wait, Zoro! That's the wrong way!

252
00:16:45.570 --> 00:16:46.570
What?!

253
00:16:46.570 --> 00:16:51.110
I said the stairs! Why the hell would you think
to go that way?! What fantasy world are you in?!

254
00:16:51.110 --> 00:16:53.870
Shut up! It was because
you didn't explain it well!

255
00:16:53.870 --> 00:16:55.490
There's no way it was my fault!

256
00:16:56.500 --> 00:16:59.500
Zoro, I'll try making some medicine...

257
00:16:59.500 --> 00:17:00.960
to cure idiocy.

258
00:17:00.960 --> 00:17:02.380
Idio– Hey!

259
00:17:02.380 --> 00:17:03.380
Chopper...

260
00:17:03.380 --> 00:17:03.840
Yeah?

261
00:17:03.840 --> 00:17:07.380
Robin my love! I'm coming now!

262
00:17:04.590 --> 00:17:06.420
Make sure it works on that guy too.

263
00:17:06.420 --> 00:17:08.920
Um... Okay, will do.

264
00:17:09.380 --> 00:17:12.180
I wonder if Big Bro will come out of this alive.

265
00:17:12.180 --> 00:17:15.560
When the going gets tough,
they're the ones that get the job done...

266
00:17:15.560 --> 00:17:19.810
probably... I'm sure... yeah...

267
00:17:20.230 --> 00:17:22.400
This is a grave crime.

268
00:17:22.400 --> 00:17:24.940
A crime of the highest magnitude!

269
00:17:24.940 --> 00:17:27.730
Then, we'll compromise and choose...

270
00:17:27.730 --> 00:17:28.940
the death penalty!

271
00:17:28.940 --> 00:17:30.070
– Agreed!
– Agreed!

272
00:17:32.450 --> 00:17:35.410
– I'm the chief justice. Don't ignore me!
– I'm the chief justice. Don't ignore me!

273
00:17:49.720 --> 00:17:51.550
Chopper. Nami. Go on ahead.

274
00:17:52.930 --> 00:17:55.800
I'll follow you after I take care of this guy.

275
00:17:56.890 --> 00:17:58.640
You think you can defeat me?

276
00:17:58.640 --> 00:18:00.640
What a cocky pirate!

277
00:18:00.640 --> 00:18:03.810
I'll show you how terrifying I can...

278
00:18:04.860 --> 00:18:05.980
Pull!

279
00:18:09.190 --> 00:18:11.400
S-Stop it!

280
00:18:12.400 --> 00:18:15.530
– Heave-ho! Heave-ho!
– Heave-ho! Heave-ho!

281
00:18:15.530 --> 00:18:17.950
S-Stop...

282
00:18:27.960 --> 00:18:30.340
We'll take you on, Cerberus!

283
00:18:30.760 --> 00:18:31.720
Franky Family!

284
00:18:33.130 --> 00:18:34.090
Let's go!

285
00:18:34.090 --> 00:18:35.890
– Ah... yeah.
– Ah... yeah.

286
00:18:36.760 --> 00:18:41.020
<b>Luffy vs. Blueno
Courthouse Rooftop</b>

287
00:18:50.690 --> 00:18:52.530
My face door finally closed!

288
00:18:52.530 --> 00:18:53.820
Naturally.

289
00:18:53.820 --> 00:18:56.410
An opened door
is meant to close.

290
00:18:56.410 --> 00:18:59.120
I am surprised you could
dodge my tempest kick.

291
00:18:59.120 --> 00:19:01.950
Yeah... because it's not that hard.

292
00:19:01.950 --> 00:19:03.460
That's regrettable.

293
00:19:07.170 --> 00:19:08.380
You jerk!

294
00:19:10.550 --> 00:19:11.250
He jumped!

295
00:19:13.760 --> 00:19:14.680
Finger Pistol!

296
00:19:15.880 --> 00:19:16.680
Shave!

297
00:19:17.760 --> 00:19:18.640
Iron Body: Smash!

298
00:19:21.560 --> 00:19:22.560
Gum-Gum...

299
00:19:23.770 --> 00:19:24.730
Bullet!

300
00:19:24.730 --> 00:19:26.100
Iron Body!

301
00:19:30.820 --> 00:19:31.570
Tempest Kick!

302
00:19:44.410 --> 00:19:47.460
He is perfectly keeping up with me.

303
00:19:47.460 --> 00:19:49.750
He altered my tempest kick's course.

304
00:19:49.750 --> 00:19:52.670
He has unbelievable physical abilities!

305
00:19:54.010 --> 00:19:54.840
This won't do.

306
00:19:56.510 --> 00:19:59.340
I'm no good like this.

307
00:20:00.300 --> 00:20:04.100
When I lost to Aokiji, I thought,

308
00:20:04.100 --> 00:20:08.440
"If I run into guys this powerful
on the sea ahead,

309
00:20:08.440 --> 00:20:10.810
I won't be able to protect my friends...

310
00:20:11.570 --> 00:20:13.440
unless I get much stronger."

311
00:20:15.280 --> 00:20:20.870
I want my friends by my side,
even if they're not all as strong as me.

312
00:20:21.410 --> 00:20:24.330
I've got to be stronger...

313
00:20:24.330 --> 00:20:26.870
or I'll lose them all.

314
00:20:26.870 --> 00:20:28.920
Then... what will you do?

315
00:20:29.620 --> 00:20:32.920
I came up with a way
to fight with all my might...

316
00:20:33.920 --> 00:20:36.260
so that I won't lose anyone...

317
00:20:39.180 --> 00:20:41.760
so that no one will be taken away from me.

318
00:20:41.760 --> 00:20:43.760
What is he doing?

319
00:20:43.760 --> 00:20:46.270
What is happening inside his body?!

320
00:20:48.520 --> 00:20:50.310
And now...

321
00:20:51.610 --> 00:20:53.480
you won't be able to keep up anymore.

322
00:20:53.480 --> 00:20:54.650
What?

323
00:20:55.360 --> 00:20:59.450
My techniques will all evolve to a new level.

324
00:21:01.570 --> 00:21:03.950
Gear Second!

325
00:21:10.800 --> 00:21:17.340
I know there’s something that I need to say,

326
00:21:17.720 --> 00:21:21.310
but I can’t seem to find the words

327
00:21:21.560 --> 00:21:29.190
Wandering aimlessly, forever on the hunt, that’s how I’ve lived

328
00:21:29.190 --> 00:21:34.950
And now there’s something right in front of me,

329
00:21:36.150 --> 00:21:39.660
a light that shines brighter than gold

330
00:21:40.030 --> 00:21:45.040
But as I trail behind, it speeds out of sight.

331
00:21:45.040 --> 00:21:51.630
What’s going on? Scared of what’s yet to come

332
00:21:51.960 --> 00:21:57.880
So many times, so many times as we both stumbled on the way

333
00:21:58.090 --> 00:22:00.890
We’ve had our highs, we’ve had our lows;

334
00:22:01.180 --> 00:22:03.970
Yeah, we just take it day by day

335
00:22:04.270 --> 00:22:10.520
Never forget that even when the night snuffs out the light

336
00:22:10.810 --> 00:22:17.150
When the dark has passed the sun will rise again
